@saynotohonorkilling

Honor Killing is often done in the name of religion, when in reality it is a cultural practice. What happens in these situations is that a person is murdered by her family because he/she ruined their reputation and thus the only way to cleanse it, is to kill him/her. In most cases, women are killed for engaging in pre-marital sex, dressing "inappropriately", talking to the opposite sex, standing up for herself to get an education, marrying outside the community, etc while men are killed for being gay. Say NO to Honor Killing. If you know someone who might be a potential victim of honor based violence, please contact local organizations that can help prevent such crimes and rehabilitate them to a safer area. 
A family's reputation isn't built by keeping a girl virgin or a boy straight. A family's reputation is built by their values. Humans are objects that can be used according to how one sees fit. Humans have their own thoughts and desires and free will to believe in what they see as right.
